{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server (file: nomad/server.go, include_tests: false, max_hops: 3)", "note": "affected_via_composition gave me ~50 direct *Server holders with exact file:line refs (nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65, nomad/stats_fetcher.go:26, nomad/autopilot.go:32, nomad/worker.go:92, nomad/drainer_shims.go:14, command/agent/agent.go:73) — these became sections A/A2/A3/A4 nearly verbatim"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces block", "note": "located 21 of the 23 narrowed-interface holders including the ones I could never have guessed at: scheduler/generic_sched.go:53 via Planner, nomad/volumewatcher/volume_watcher.go:22 via CSIVolumeRPC, nomad/drainer/drainer.go:132 via RaftApplier, nomad/auth/auth.go:43 via Encrypter, client/widmgr/signer.go:37 via RPCer — each with the carrier and the chain to Server, which is exactly section B"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — chain field on auth.Authenticator", "note": "the chain 'nomad.Encrypter > nomad.Server' told me Authenticator is two hops out, which I wrote directly into B6 without tracing it myself"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server, direction=callers", "note": "confirmed the Server type's own definition site nomad/server.go:116 and the composed_by set, which cross-checked the blast composition list"},
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query": "(no args)", "note": "confirmed the index was fresh (pending 0, watching) and Go coverage was full-tier, so I trusted the composition list as near-complete rather than re-walking the package"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Nomad server struct cluster server object", "note": "did not return nomad.Server itself — top hits were structs.ServerMember, ServerMembersResponse, Status, nodeConnState. I only got the real root type (nomad/server.go:116) from the sense_graph call I fired in parallel. The semantic search whiffed on the single most important symbol in the query"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces", "note": "MISSED the entire deploymentwatcher group: deployments_watcher.go:76/82/85 (DeploymentRaftEndpoints, DeploymentRPC, JobRPC), the two embedded interfaces on deploymentWatcher at deployment_watcher.go:69/73, and deployment_watcher_shims.go:15 (apply raftApplyFn). Six holders — the highest-risk ones in the whole audit — absent. It also included two test holders (nomad/leader_test.go:445, nomad/worker_test.go:32) despite include_tests:false"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces", "note": "listed helper/raftutil/fsm.go:29 as retaining Server via nomadFSM, but that is offline snapshot tooling with no live Server; I had to reason it out and exclude it explicitly in B8"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "field line numbers were struct-declaration lines, not the retaining-field lines the ticket asked for (e.g. gave nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65 for the type, field srv is at :66; scheduler/generic_sched.go:53 vs planner at :57). Every single line in my final answer had to be re-derived with grep"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "the retaining FIELD line. I ran a for-loop grep over all 17 listed files matching '^\\s+[a-zA-Z_]+ +(RPCer|RPCHandler|nomadFSM|Encrypter|RaftApplier|JobEvalDispatcher|CSIVolumeRPC|Planner)' to get the real numbers (alloc_watcher.go:66, drainer.go:116/159, periodic.go:27, structs.go:76). The ticket demanded field-level file:line and Sense only pins the enclosing type"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "that first grep returned NOTHING for alloc_runner.go, csi_hook.go, and all three scheduler files, because the fields are qualified (config.RPCer, sstructs.Planner) and my pattern assumed bare names — a second grep found alloc_runner.go:206 and generic_sched.go:57. Sense had told me the interface name but not the qualified type as written at the field"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — deploymentwatcher absent", "fallback": "grep + read", "missing": "the entire deploymentwatcher subsystem. I grepped nomad/deploymentwatcher/*.go for retaining fields, then sed-read deployments_watcher.go:80-95 and server.go:1155-1180 to find setupDeploymentWatcher and the raftApplyFn shim. Nothing in any Sense response pointed at this package"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "a completeness backstop for direct fields. I ran a repo-wide grep for '\\tsrv \\*Server|\\ts \\*Server|\\tserver \\*Server' to verify the composition list, which is how I caught that StatsFetcher uses localServer (stats_fetcher.go:29) and AutopilotDelegate uses server — field names the composition list never showed"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "function-value retention. I grepped raftApplyFn to find server.go:1161 'apply: s.raftApply'. Sense's own index_caveat admits it misses 'function-value passing (handlers stored as fields)' — accurate self-report, but it meant the riskiest holder in the audit was invisible"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server — retained_via_interfaces on client/config", "fallback": "read", "missing": "which concrete type actually lands at runtime. Sense's carrier said agent.Agent for all the client/ RPCer holders, but I had to read client/config/arconfig.go:36 and command/agent/http.go:99-115 to establish that on a client-only agent the satisfier is *client.Client, not the Server — a conditional I had to write into B7"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "sense_blast symbol=nomad.Server", "query_after": "added file='nomad/server.go' and include_tests=false to the same call", "hint": "CLAUDE.md's routing table plus the sense_blast schema's own 'file: Disambiguate by file path substring when the symbol name is ambiguous' — I preemptively pinned the file because 'Server' is a name that recurs across the Nomad tree"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "trusting retained_via_interfaces as the complete narrowed-holder set", "query_after": "grep sweep over nomad/ client/ scheduler/ for shim types and 'set of Server methods' comments, then targeted reads of setupDeploymentWatcher", "hint": "the retained_note ('each row may retain Server, one interface indirection deep... Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified') plus completeness.verdict='partial' with hidden=140 and truncated=true — that explicit one-hop bound is what told me a two-hop holder like the deploymentwatcher shim chain could be missing, and it was"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "relying on the composition list alone for direct fields", "query_after": "repo-wide grep for '\\tsrv \\*Server' variants as a backstop", "hint": "index_caveat: 'Static graph may miss: method-on-field dispatch (c.engine.X), function-value passing (handlers stored as fields)' — this directly motivated the raftApplyFn grep that found deployment_watcher_shims.go:15"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast. It is the exact query this ticket asks and nothing else answers it: 21 holders whose files never import the nomad package and never name Server, each with the interface name, a concrete carrier, and the containment chain back to Server. scheduler/generic_sched.go via Planner→Worker→srv, nomad/auth/auth.go via Encrypter→srv, nomad/drainer/drainer.go via RaftApplier→drainerShim→s — I could not have assembled that set with grep in this session, because there is no string common to those files to grep for. It converted an open-ended 'find every hidden holder' hunt into a list I could verify.",
  "q5_improve": "Emit the retaining FIELD's file:line and its type as written, not the enclosing type's declaration line. Every one of the ~70 holders in my answer needed a grep to convert 'nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65' into 'srv *Server at :66' and 'scheduler/generic_sched.go:53' into 'planner sstructs.Planner at :57' — and my first field-grep silently missed six files because I guessed bare interface names when the source writes config.RPCer and sstructs.Planner. Sense already parsed those fields to build the composition and retained_via_interfaces edges; surfacing field_name, field_type_as_written, and field_ref would have removed every fallback in Q2 except the deploymentwatcher gap. Second, honour include_tests=false in retained_via_interfaces (it leaked leader_test.go:445 and worker_test.go:32), and consider following shim chains two hops so raftApplyFn-style bound-method retention surfaces.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "retained_via_interfaces gave me 21 narrowed holders across six packages that share no greppable string and were genuinely unrecoverable otherwise (Q1, Q4), and its own retained_note and index_caveat correctly steered me to the fallbacks that found the rest (Q3) — but it missed the six highest-risk deploymentwatcher holders entirely, leaked test holders against include_tests=false, and pinned type-declaration lines instead of field lines, so every cited line in my deliverable still came from grep (Q2), which is squarely the 'faster, but I needed fallbacks to finish' band rather than the 9-10 one."
}

